{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"16a38e53-2749-4eeb-80d2-bac5b450e104","content":"The issue is the **file compilation order** in the `.fsproj`. In F#, files can only reference modules defined in files listed *above* them. `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`, but is listed before it.\n\nFixing by reordering:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_KYn5hQnmDCtCNxO3FmWc4U","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-07eb6f3eee8347578fc9f82e2851535e/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>","new_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-07eb6f3eee8347578fc9f82e2851535e/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"f83dfb6e-63b5-403d-86ef-3702877264c0","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file order matters — files can only reference types/modules defined in files that appear *before* them in the compilation order. \n\nLooking at the `.fsproj`:\n1. `Services.fs` (listed first) — depends on `Domain.fs` (`open BrokenOrder.Domain`)\n2. `Domain.fs` (listed second) — defines `Domain` types\n3. `Program.fs` (listed third) — depends on both\n\nThe problem is that `Services.fs` is listed before `Domain.fs`, but `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`. The correct order should be:\n\n\n1. `Domain.fs` (no dependencies)\n2. `Services.fs` (depends on Domain)\n3. `Program.fs` (depends on both)","outputTokens":478,"requestId":"041E:23C36A:C652E0:E49EEC:69F2A7EC"},"id":"f22e9e8e-3f46-4639-b08c-8bf8442e0caf","timestamp":"2026-04-30T00:53:07.836Z","parentId":"af1a6b4e-4e71-46c0-a48d-37c78faa9b19"}
